story.title: Unknown Caller - Episode 2
story.storyDescription: This Halloween, someone from Kelly’s past wants revenge – someone who knows her deepest, darkest secret.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Tamara Mataya is a New York Times and USA Today bestselling author,  a ghostwriter, a librarian, and a musician with synesthesia. She puts the S in TWSS and the B in LGBTQIA+.

story.prePaywallNotification: One night ruined Kelly’s life forever. Find out what happened in UNKNOWN CALLER.
story.postPaywallNotification: OMG: Is Kelly a murderer?!! Find out by reading the rest of UNKNOWN CALLER.

messages.text: Who is that in the picture?
Why are you showing me this picture?
Let’s talk about how you knew that girl instead.
And the last time you saw her was on Halloween night two years ago.
And why do you care about some woman in a picture?
Now I want you to say her name.
Good girl. Doesn’t it feel better to stop pretending you have no idea who she is?
Of course I know who she is.
You got me on a technicality.
Look, I’m not her, if that’s what you’re thinking.
I’m not Violet in the witness protection program or something.
Are you some kind of stalker trying to track her down?
Because if so, I don’t know where she is.
We can call it a night right now.
You don’t know where she is?
I don’t! And I’m not her, if that’s your game.
You think I’m Violet and moved and changed my name to Kelly.
And you’re trying to make me admit I’m her.
Oh, this isn’t a case of mistaken identity.
Screw you! I’m done with this!
I think I preferred it when you were flirting with me.
Elaborate on how you knew Violet.
We went to school together. College.
Go on. You went to college with Violet.
We went to school together back East.
A couple years ago. I graduated and moved away.
I thought you wanted the truth, not stories?
I like TRUE stories. Even on Halloween.
You went to college with her…until she went MISSING.
And we both know she was more to you than some chick you went to school with.
A lot of people knew her. She was popular.
You’re deflecting. Stop pretending you don’t know her.
There will be consequences if you continue to lie.
You…why does it matter if I knew her? Who is she to you?
Ah, that’s two questions. I’ll answer the first.
Nope. My turn. How well did you know Violet?
You don’t sleep in a tiny room with someone for a year without getting close.
How good of friends would you say you were?
We were…I wanted to be her best friend.
When did you first realize that you wanted Violet to be your bestie?
I don’t know. We just started talking.
No, there was ONE night that changed things.
Jarod. She dried my tears, we dressed up and went out.
To a costume party Violet knew about.
I told you. I know everything.
Say thank you. I gave you that for free.
Would you say your relationship was defined by that night?
With her taking care of you, drawing you into her circle of friends?
I suppose so, yes. Until that night, she’d never really had time for me.
I didn’t like it when she ignored me, but whatever.
Did you come to care for her?
Or were you just pretending you liked her
Yes. Yes I CARED, I never pretended about that!
You seemed to care about a lot of people that night.
It was a party on Halloween!
You dressed as a cat and wore a skimpy black top.
All the guys’ eyes were on you.
That’s what you’re supposed to be figuring out.
Call the police. I’m sure they’d love to hear your confession.
You’ve got me confused with someone else.
Have you ever seen a dead body?
It was taken the night Violet went missing.
How did you get this picture?
If you contact anyone else in any way
I will tell EVERYONE what you did.
